objects.name: cyclops blink
objects.description: Cyclops Blink is a malicious Linux ELF executable, compiled for the 32-bit PowerPC (big-endian) architecture. It implements a modular framework consisting of a core component and additional modules that are executed as child processes.

objects.name: FBI
objects.description: Federal Bureau of Investigation, involved in the analysis of Cyclops Blink.

objects.name: CISA
objects.description: Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency, involved in the analysis of Cyclops Blink.

objects.name: NSA
objects.description: National Security Agency, involved in the analysis of Cyclops Blink.

objects.name: Command and Scripting Interpreter: Unix Shell
objects.description: Cyclops Blink executes downloaded files using the Linux API function execlp.

objects.name: Boot or Logon Initialization Scripts: RC Scripts
objects.description: Cyclops Blink is executed on device startup, using a modified S51armled RC script.

objects.name: Pre-OS Boot: System Firmware
objects.description: Cyclops Blink maintains persistence throughout the legitimate device firmware update process.

objects.name: Impair Defenses: Disable or Modify System Firewall
objects.description: Cyclops Blink modifies the Linux iptables firewall to enable C2 communication via a stored list of port numbers.

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_notable_strings
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_notable_strings { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects notable strings identified within the Cyclops Blink executable" date = "2022-02-23" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" strings: $proc_name1 = "[kworker/0:1]" $proc_name2 = "[kworker/1:1]" $dns_query = "POST /dns-query HTTP/1.1\x0d\x0aHost: dns.google\x0d\x0a" $iptables1 = "iptables -I %s -p tcp --dport %d -j ACCEPT &>/dev/null" $iptables2 = "iptables -D %s -p tcp --dport %d -j ACCEPT &>/dev/null" $sys_recon1 = "{\"ver\":\"%x\",\"mods\";[" $sys_recon2 = "uptime: %lu mem_size: %lu mem_free: %lu" $sys_recon3 = "disk_size: %lu disk_free: %lu" $sys_recon4 = "hw: %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x" $testpath = "%s/214688dsf46" $confpath = "%s/rootfs_cfg" $downpath = "/var/tmp/a.tmp" condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and (8 of them) }

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_module_initialisation
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_module_initialisation { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects the code bytes used to initialise the modules built into Cyclops Blink" date = "2022-02-23" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" strings: $ = {94 21 FF F0 93 E1 00 08 7C 3F 0B 78 38 00 00 ?? 7C 03 03 78 81 61 00 00 8E EB FF F8 7D 61 5B 78 4E 80 00 20} condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and (any of them) }
